Hi everyone,
 
I've started a small GPL C# demonstration program on SourceForge to show how
a Factory Pattern might be used to generate and compile HyperNEAT on CUDA
(NVidia's Compute Unified Device Architecture). This is just a part-time
personal project (nights and weekends).
 
http://sourceforge.net/projects/hyperneat4cuda
 
It will probably take me a couple of days to a week to get everything
uploaded.  I've also blocked out a TeX paper to describe the concepts,
challenges and points of interest.
 
Ken Lloyd
 
============================
Kenneth A. Lloyd
CEO - Director of Systems Science
Watt Systems Technologies Inc.
Albuquerque, NM USA
 
kenneth.lloyd[at]wattsys.com
kenneth.lloyd[at]incose.org     Research Director - MBSE of Complex,
Adaptive and Stochastic Systems
kenneth.lloyd[at]nmug.net      
 <http://www.wattsys.com/> www.wattsys.com
 
 <http://www.linkedin.com/pub/7/9a/824> http://www.linkedin.com/pub/7/9a/824
 
http://kenscomplex.blogspot.com/
